00004 /*
00005  * Octeon Trace logs are recorded in a ring buffer as TVs by the traced cores
00006  * and consumed by the master. This buffer is allocated/freed on demand.
00007  * The first int records the head and the 2nd the tail.
00008  */
00009 #define OCTEON_TRACE_LOG_BUF_LEN    1024
00010 #define OCTEON_TRACE_LOG_NBLOCK(block_name, core)           \
00011     do {                                \
00012         sprintf((block_name), "otl_queue%d", (core));       \
00013     } while (0)
00014 #define OCTEON_TRACE_LOG_NEXT(pos)                  \
00015     (((pos) + 1) % OCTEON_TRACE_LOG_BUF_LEN)
